  footnotes: []
english:
  title: On the Way Through Samjeondo
  author: Seo Geo-jeong
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Riding a weary horse toward Samjeondo,
    the west wind tilts my hat askew.
    The clear river holds the departing geese,
    the setting sun escorts the returning crows.

    On ancient trees, autumn leaves gleam bright,
    in a lonely village, white sand appears.
    Where the blue mountains begin to fade,
    far off, I recognize—that is my home.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: Samjeondo (三田渡) is a historical site in Korea, located near present-day Seoul on the Han River. The title suggests a journey through this place.
  - key: ''
    value: The poem employs the traditional poetic device of using natural imagery—geese, crows, autumn leaves, and sand—to create a mood of melancholy return and nostalgic recognition.
